<HEADLINE> Buchberger Named Thrashers Captain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Kelly Buchberger, who spent the last four years  
as captain of the Edmonton Oilers, will be the first captain for 
the expansion Atlanta Thrashers. 
</P>
<P>
	The team named Buchberger captain on Tuesday, a move widely  
expected since the 32-year-old right wing was acquired from 
Edmonton in the expansion draft. 
</P>
<P>
	Also, the Thrashers assigned goaltender Corey Schwab to Orlando  
of the IHL. Atlanta will have to cut six more players before 
Saturday night's opener against New Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	Buchberger spent 13 seasons with the Oilers, playing on three  
Stanley Cup teams and taking over as captain in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Schwab, who played 40 games last season for Tampa Bay, provides  
minor-league insurance for the Thrashers. The top two goalies are 
Damian Rhodes and Norm Maracle. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
