<HEADLINE> CMGI To Acquire 1stUp.com </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANDOVER, Mass. (AP) -- CMGI Inc., an Internet holding company,  
announced it is acquiring 1stUp.com, which provides businesses with 
the ability to offer free, advertising-supported Internet access. 
</P>
<P>
	1stUp.com, based in San Francisco, currently offers its free  
Internet access to AltaVista, a search engine portal owned by CMGI. 
Terms of the acquisition were not disclosed, the companies said 
Monday in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	CMGI, based in Andover, has been acquiring Internet companies in  
an effort to create a network large enough to challenge America 
Online Inc. and Yahoo! Inc. Recently, CMGI bought AdForce, an 
Internet advertising service firm and Signatures Network, a music 
and celebrity licensing and event merchandising company. 



  	   	
