<HEADLINE> Gehry To Deisgn New Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Architect Frank O. Gehry, who designed the  
ultramodern Guggenheim museum in Bilbao, Spain, has been hired 
again by Guggenheim, this time for a dramatic new building here. 
</P>
<P>
	Gehry has designed a building that rises about 45 stories out of  
a cloud-like shape, The New York Times reported Tuesday, citing an 
internal Guggenheim memo and unidentified officials. 
</P>
<P>
	The structure would be on a platform above piers along the East  
River near Wall Street in lower Manhattan and include exhibition 
space, a theater and a skating rink. 
</P>
<P>
	The proposal is one of nine the city is considering for the  
site; a decision is expected within a few months. 
</P>
<P>
	Museum and city officials wouldn't comment on the proposal.  
</P>
<P>
	Gehry designed the $100 million Guggenheim museum in Bilbao. Its  
big plunging, curved forms are considered one of the world's most 
important works of contemporary architecture. 
  	   	
