<HEADLINE> Lightning's Daigle May Go to Minors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Former first overall draft pick Alexandre  
Daigle was designated for assignment Tuesday by the Tampa Bay 
Lightning. 
</P>
<P>
	The move was not unexpected after Tampa Bay left the winger  
unprotected for last Monday's waiver draft. As a result, Daigle is 
expected to be assigned to a minor league team. 
</P>
<P>
	``You get out what you put in,'' Tampa Bay coach Steve Ludzik  
said Saturday after the team opted not to protect Daigle in the 
waiver draft. 
</P>
<P>
	Daigle was taken first overall in the 1993 draft by Ottawa.  
Since that time, his work ethic has come into question. He has 92 
goals and 215 points in 401 NHL games. 
</P>
<P>
	Daigle was acquired by the Lightning as part of a three-team  
trade last Jan. 29. He also played for Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
	Tampa Bay also designated defenseman Jassen Cullimore for  
assignment. Wingers Andy Bezeau, Kyle Freadrich and Steve Walker 
were sent to Detroit of the International Hockey League. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
