<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-28 12:40:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Trump Hits Snag in TV Show Taping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Donald Trump has town officials in a  
huff over a home-decorating TV show filmed at his Mar-a-Lago 
estate. 
</P>
<P>
	It seems Trump ran afoul of the upscale island's rules again,  
this time violating an ordinance against commercial filming in a 
residential area by allowing the cozy home and garden show ``It's a 
Snap'' into his lavish estate. 
</P>
<P>
	Chief code enforcement officer Brian House gave Trump a cease  
and desist order Monday. Trump agreed, and he will not be taken 
before the town board. 
</P>
<P>
	That means the second episode of the show filmed at Mar-a-Lago  
will not be aired as planned Friday on the South Florida PaxNet 
stations. 
</P>
<P>
	Trump could face a $250 fine if the show is broadcast.  
</P>
<P>
	In 1994, Trump got a warning after allowing a magazine shoot at  
Mar-a-Lago. He also has a long history of legal battles with the 
town council over restrictions on his private club. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
