<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bauer: Affair Gossip Is Outrage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Republican presidential hopeful Gary Bauer  
dismissed a gossip item about an alleged affair as ``disgusting'' 
and ``outrageous.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The New York Daily News ran a gossip column Monday that read:  
``What presidential candidate is praying that a former secretary 
doesn't go public with her claim that he's been having an affair 
with a twentysomething woman?'' 
</P>
<P>
	Interviewed by the San Francisco Chronicle after the gossip  
piece appeared Monday, Bauer said he thought the Daily News was 
referring to him. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think it's supposed to be me. And it's disgusting,'' Bauer  
said. ``It almost makes me physically sick. My wife and I have been 
married for 27 years ... I have been loyal to her, and she's been 
loyal to me all those years.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Asked who might be the source of the rumors, Bauer refused to be  
specific but said, ``I think it's coming from the camp of one of my 
political opponents.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bauer planned a news conference Wednesday.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
