<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Recruiting Goals for Armed Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	All branches of the U.S. military set recruitment goals to  
maintain forces at needed levels. The goals are changed each year 
according to service needs, recruitment success in the previous 
year, retention of current military personnel and other factors. 
</P>
<P>
	Goals for each service in recruiting men and women without prior  
military service and what they now expect to achieve by the end of 
the fiscal year, Sept. 30: 
</P>
<P>
	--Air Force: Goal 33,800, expect 32,100, or 1,700 short.  
</P>
<P>
	--Army: Goal 74,500, expect to recruit 68,200, or 6,300 short.  
</P>
<P>
	--Marines: Goal 35,615, more than 35,700 to meet goal.  
</P>
<P>
	--Navy: Goal 53,200, expect 53,200 or more to meet goal,  
</P>
<P>
	The total needed is 197,115 recruits needed to maintain a force  
of 1.4 million. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
