<HEADLINE> Rambis Gets New Job With Lakers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Kurt Rambis, who has held a variety of  
jobs with the Los Angeles Lakers, got a new post Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Rambis, a former player, assistant coach and head coach with Los  
Angeles, is now advisor to the president-basketball. 
</P>
<P>
	The position will involve Rambis' working with team owner and  
president Jerry Buss, executive vice president Jerry West, and 
general manager Mitch Kupchak. 
</P>
<P>
	``Except for a few years at the end of his playing career when  
he was with other teams, Kurt Rambis has been a mainstay in the 
Lakers' organization since 1981,'' Kupchak said. ``We're pleased 
that he will remain part of the organization.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rambis served as Los Angeles' interim coach after Del Harris was  
fired during the lockout-shortened 1999 season. Rambis was not 
retained in that job because the Lakers hired Phil Jackson as coach 
after the season ended. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
