<HEADLINE> Bradley Health Care Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Highlights of Democratic presidential hopeful Bill Bradley's  
health care proposal: 
</P>
<P>
	-- Requires parents to buy health insurance for children.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Offers discounted premiums to low and middle-income families.  
Poor adults also would be eligible for subsidies. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Expands Medicare to provide the elderly with uncapped  
prescription drug benefits for chronic or catastrophic illnesses. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Provides a system of integrated medical and social services --  
such as housekeeping and transportation -- to cut down on 
nursing-home admissions. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Allows adults to buy into the health plan provided to members  
of Congress and 9 million federal employees. 
</P>
<P>
	-- Total cost: $55 to $65 billion  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
