<HEADLINE> Miami U. Loses Johnson to Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OXFORD, Ohio (AP) -- Miami University lost its top receiver, Sly  
Johnson, to a knee injury as the team prepares to play No. 17 
Marshall on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson, a junior, is out indefinitely with a torn anterior  
cruciate ligament in his right knee. He was injured during the 
first quarter of last Saturday's game at Central Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
	He was second in the nation with 145.3 receiving yards per game  
going into last weekend's games, and was on pace to set numerous 
school receiving records this season. 
</P>
<P>
	``He had worked so hard in the offseason and was really having a  
special season,'' Miami coach Terry Hoeppner said. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson caught 16 passes for the Redhawks (3-1) this season,  
including six for 50 or more yards. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami officials gave no indication of when Johnson might be able  
to play football again. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
