<HEADLINE> Billy Crystal Buys Mantle's Glove </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Billy Crystal once wanted to be Mickey Mantle.  
Now, at least, he's got the glove. 
</P>
<P>
	Crystal bought one of Mantle's old gloves at a Sotheby's auction  
of baseball memorabilia Monday for $239,000, far exceeding its 
pre-sale estimate of $10,000 to $20,000. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yankees legend wore the glove around 1960.  
</P>
<P>
	At an unveiling of a red granite monument to honor Mantle in  
1996, Crystal recalled how as a 9-year-old boy in 1956 he watched 
in awe as Mantle blasted a home run off the right-field facade at 
Yankee Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	``That day,'' Crystal said, ``I knew I wanted to play baseball.  
I wanted to be Mickey Mantle.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mantle died in 1995.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
