<HEADLINE> Va. Cop Admits to Molesting Boys </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAWRENCEVILLE, Va. (AP) -- The police chief of a rural farming  
town and a local electrician admitted molesting seven boys between 
the ages of 9 and 16. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark D. Harvey, 30, the police chief of Alberta for three years,  
pleaded guilty Monday to 13 charges of forcible sodomy and 
aggravated sexual assault. The assaults took place between December 
1997 and February. 
</P>
<P>
	Michael Lee Knight, 41, pleaded guilty to 14 similar counts.  
Prosecutors dropped other charges against the two as part of a plea 
agreement. Both men face up to life in prison on the charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Harvey was placed on unpaid suspension after his arrest. His  
lawyer declined to comment after the court session. 
</P>
<P>
	The victims were in court and prepared to testify, said Betsy  
Draper, director of the Brunswick County Victim and Witness 
Assistance Program. 
</P>
<P>
	With the plea deal, ``I think they were relieved,'' Ms. Draper  
said. ``There are no happy people in a case like this.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Brunswick County Commonwealth's Attorney Lezlie Green said the  
molesting was ``in every sense of the word a joint enterprise'' 
between Harvey and Knight, adding that both men were frequently 
present when the sex acts with the boys took place. 
</P>
<P>
	She said Knight showed at least one of his victims a knife,  
threatening to stab him if the child told what was going on. He 
also gave at least some of the children muscle relaxers and 
alcohol, she said in court. 
</P>
<P>
	In some cases, unsuspecting parents allowed their boys to stay  
with Harvey overnight in advance of outings such as fishing or 
baseball, she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Sentencing was scheduled for Dec. 16.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
