<HEADLINE> Woman in Gifford Scandal Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- The woman whose romantic interlude  
with Frank Gifford found its way to the tabloid front pages has 
been arrested on a charge of drunken driving. 
</P>
<P>
	Suzen Johnson was arrested Sept. 7 after the car she was driving  
rear-ended a pickup truck, according to Boca Raton police reports. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson, 48, had a 0.17 blood-alcohol level, nearly twice the  
legal limit, according to police. She was booked on a charge of 
driving while intoxicated, released and is due back in court 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Her husband, Harold Johnson, told The Palm Beach Post that his  
wife, a flight attendant, was not drunk. She had been treated 
earlier in the day by an orthopedic surgeon for a swollen foot 
caused by a luggage spill at work, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	``He gave her some pills,'' Johnson said. ``She simply had a  
couple glasses of wine. She doesn't drink that much.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Suzen Johnson has a $10 million lawsuit pending against the  
parent company of the Globe tabloid, claiming the paper 
choreographed the scandal with Gifford and pressured her into 
seducing him. 
</P>
<P>
	The Globe has acknowledged paying her at least $75,000 for  
setting up the rendezvous in a New York hotel two years ago. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
