<HEADLINE> Sosa's Wife Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The wife of Chicago Cubs slugger Sammy Sosa was  
admitted to a hospital emergency room with an undisclosed illness 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Sonia Sosa, 25, arrived at the Northwestern Memorial Hospital  
about 5 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
	``She is in good condition and doing well,'' hospital spokesman  
Stuart Greenblatt said, adding there was no timetable for her 
release. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither the team nor hospital spokesmen would comment on  
broadcast reports that Sonia Sosa was ill after drinking beer and 
taking prescription medication. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa, tied with Mark McGwire of the St. Louis Cardinals for the  
major league home run lead with 61, was with his team in 
Philadelphia. Cubs spokesman Benji De La Fuente said there were no 
plans for Sosa to return to Chicago to be with his wife. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
